content.description: At the downstream side of the WTF, a boulder sitting atop two others forms a roof crack. Start all the way at the far end with feet almost out the other side and climb the overhanging crack to a strenuous topout. Beware of the questionable quartz jugs.
content.protection: A pad can be shoved into the slot, but won't help much.
content.location: Find the log in the streambed and you're there.

content.description: Start on the incredible jugs of a quartz band. Climb up right through slot and top out. A foot in the roof helps to get going.
content.location: In the "room" this will be on the upstream side of the central boulder.

content.description: The central streambed of the Peanut Boulders area weaves through a collection of boulders about 50 yards behind (north) the Dark Matter Boulder. The WTF Boulder is most notoriously recognizable by several pebbles epoxied onto its blank-ish east face.   To get there, hike between the DM and Nacho boulders heading for the wash; stay left out of the thickest brush. After intersecting the wash, turn right, heading back downstream and scramble down between two boulders entering a small flat, gravel-bottomed room. Alternately follow the wash upstream from DM.
